main event: A civilian observer reported seeing two round, reddish-orange objects hovering in the sky over Cincinnati, Ohio on August 20, 1968.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be bright and luminous, with one object appearing larger than the other at times.
The objects were estimated to be approximately 50-100 feet in diameter and flying at an altitude of 500-1000 feet.
The objects hovered for about 5 minutes before gradually climbing and flying out of sight towards the southwest.
The observer noted that the objects appeared to be maneuvering.
The observer had not seen a similar phenomenon before.
